{
  "texts": [
    "At best, the addition of strengths has a balancing effect to make trainees not feel depressive about their overall competence\" (ten Cate, 2013).",
    "The highly informative feedback gives participants more details on task performance than the minimal feedback.",
    "This also bears the possibility that more discrepancies between participants' actual and perceived performance will be pointed out.",
    "If these discrepancies are too large, and the resulting feedback is unexpectedly negative, this might hurt participants' feelings of competence, decreasing their intrinsic motivation.",
    "This assumption is also in line with empirical results."
  ]
}